args:
The prince and his friends meet Xuan Zang of
the Qilin tribe. Along with her pupil, Wu Kong,
and the dragon Yulong, she is on a journey
to seal away dangerous antique relics.
Once they learn the danger such relics pose,
the party sets off for a nearby Qilin village.
Good thing we showed up when we did.\nI heard the fiends here were outta control,\nbut this is nine kinds'a batcrap!
Hey, no worries about ol' me!\nJust got distracted there for a second.
These are no normal fiends; I sense\na great power lurking within them.
Right?! Ya cut 'em, ya stab 'em,\nand they don't seem to give a damn.\nI might as well be fightin' air!
The heck is going ON here?!
We won't get anywhere at this rate.
But we can't just ignore these fiends!
O power universal! Dispel the false faces\nof these fiends, and grant us the ability\nto strike fair and true!
I know not what that woman did, but our\nattacks appear to be landing now.
We can figure out the details later.\nLet's finish this!
My master said to stand aside, yeah?\nJust hang back.
I shan't be disappointed, should you\nentrust the situation to her.
Encircle their bodies, O fetters!\nSeal them with all haste!
Wait, so they WERE illusions?\nMan, I am so confused right now...
Oh, they were no illusion. Rather,\nthey were the product of a Qilin relic.
Oooooh, riiiiight! Now I get it!\n...Wait, no. I don't get ANYTHING.
Aw, don't worry about it. Your little brains\nwould probably leak outta your ears if\nwe tried to explain it to you.
Yer brains are gonna be leakin' when\nI bash yer snot-nosed little face in!

Do you know who you're dealing with,
pops? We'll kick your butt from here
to the graveyard and then shove ya
in a fresh hole!
You are as crude as ever. Hardly befitting\na pupil of Xuan Zang.
You have my apologies for my\npupil's impulsive tongue.

Pray forgive the delay in introductions.
I am a traveler called Xuan Zang.
The young one is my pupil, Wu Kong,
and the other is my attendant, Yulong.
Excuse me, Xuan Zang, but your clothing\nis familiar. You're of the Qilin tribe, yes?
The tribe so elusive that most believe\nthem rumors? What are the chances\nwe'd find someone like that out here?
That might be overselling things a bit,\nalthough travelers like me are indeed\nrare among the Qilin.
I am what we call a sealer.
Wait, you train seals? That's AWESOME!
Not even close! Those selected to be\nsealers are the most amazing people\nyou can imagine, even among the Qilin!
It's not boasting if it's TRUE, master!\nSheesh, you really are an old\nstick-in-the-mud sometimes.

And such power comes with responsibility,
hence why I continue to attempt to teach
you discipline. You cannot possibly hope to
handle the Qilin relics otherwise.
Tch! Aw, c'mon! Not this again!\nYou know I can handle those relics!
So, uh, we're a little in the dark\non this whole ï¼‚relic sealerï¼‚ thing.

Yes, of course. Put simply, there are a
number of ancient artifacts that contain
great and frightening powers. We call
these artifacts ï¼‚Qilin relics.ï¼‚
I have heard rumors of these relics.\nThey are said to hold a vast number\nof mysterious capabilities.
However, even though the relics can be\na boon to society, they become profoundly\ndangerous when misused.
Those fiends you couldn't put a dent in\nearlier were created by a Qilin relic.
If these relics can MAKE fiends,\nthey are even more dangerous\nthan your description implied.
Which is why we sealers are charged\nwith seeking out and neutralizing them.
We've come from waaaaay out east,\nstopping here and there to snatch up\nany relics we find.
We were actually just on our way to\na Qilin village in Alberia to seal up\na few of the relics we gathered.
There is a Qilin village in Alberia?!
How come I ain't never heard of it?!
It is no surprise you are unaware of its\nexistence, for Qilin use the power of the\nrelics to hide their villages from outsiders.
*snicker* Yeah, she means bozos\ncan't see it! Aaaah ha ha ha ha!
I'm gonna use yer head for a punchin' bag!
Uh oh! Did I touch a nerve?
Sorry master, but the library is open and\nI am READING this blockhead here.\nI'll get back to you in juuust aâ€”
A mouth is not a river that is free to run\nas it will. It must be controlled.
I'm sorry, master! And please allow me to\napologize to all of you as well!
Well that was a sudden switch.\nAlmost weird how polite yer bein' now.
Look, you don't know what\nshe's like when she's angry....
Uh, master? You know I hate it when you\nstart doing your creepy laugh like that.
Come, Wu Kong. Come, Yulong.\nLet us take our leave.
Would you like to ride upon my back,\nXuan Zang? Only if it please you,\nof course.
Wait, hold on. I know we just met,\nbut would you mind if we came along?

We wouldn't have defeated those fiends
earlier without help. If these Qilin relics
are doing such things in my homeland,
I want to learn more about them.
Yeah, I got no interest in fightin'\na buncha fiend ghosts again.
The choice is yours, Xuan Zang.\nWould you mind?
I suppose that would be all right.
Whaaaaat?! But you said we aren't\nsupposed to tell people too much\nabout the relics...

It is the duty of a sealer to ensure not only
that the relics are properly taken care of,
but also that any chaos caused by them is
dispelled from the world.

As such, it could be argued that teaching
those who fight for the good of the people
more about their existence and abilities
is also a sealer's duty.
Furthermore...I have a feeling we can\ntrust these people.
However! Be warned that the journey\nahead will be a harsh one.
There's no hardship we won't face for the\nsake of our people. Come on, everyone!
